    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-30T04:43:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-30T04:43:00-05:00" n="682"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d682">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5621</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-30T09:00:00-00:43">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1917, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 1.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President of Liberia issued a proclamation yesterday afternoon practically in the
                    terms of the Legation’s June 15, 10 a.m., and <pb facs="0643" n="471"
                        xml:id="pg_471"/> made application to any transaction affecting the property
                    of German firms in Liberia subsequent to last May 8 with heavy penalty attached,
                    also formally notifying German subjects that they must leave Liberia at the
                    earliest possible moment.</p>
                <p>As soon as advised, war will be declared and deportation effected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
